  "articleSummary": "The article argues that model rankings and benchmarks are irrelevant for security agents, which require a model router that selects the best model per task based on cost, quality, and failure modes. The author presents evals from a product-shaped suite testing security discovery, planning, tool use, and integration across seven model routes (e.g., GPT-5.6 Sol, Gemini 3.5 Flash, DeepSeek V4 Flash). Key results show cheap models like DeepSeek Flash can be highly effective (410/425 at $0.005), while premium models don't always outperform; the focus is on the cost-quality frontier and \"guard failures.\" The tone is analytical and engineering-focused, using framing like \"routing problem vs. leaderboard problem\" and \"start with the frontier, then escalate,\" aimed at practitioners building agentic security systems.",
